<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-25T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-25T12:00:00-05:00" n="118" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d118">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/705a: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-25T13:00:00-04:00">May
                                        25, 1940—1 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>136. In view of the uncertainties of the moment and our great concern
                                for the safety of American citizens and ships in the Mediterranean
                                the Department requests that you approach Ciano informally and <pb facs="0116" n="107" xml:id="pg_107"/> confidentially and state
                                that we would appreciate being kept closely informed of any
                                developments which would affect these American citizens and
                                ships.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>